<subSubSection id="42C665024308281CFD3CB51AFB5BE274" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0A6336894308281CFD3CB51AFB58E49D" blockId="7.[707,1194,751,1357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFD3CB51AFCB8E403" bold="true" box="[743,841,805,826]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Remarks.</emphasis>
Say’ s 
<typeStatus id="D567882B4308281CFC57B51AFC46E403" box="[908,951,805,826]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">type</typeStatus>
, reported as found “near the Rocky Mountains”, is not extant (
<bibRefCitation id="6E4D4B784308281CFB99B500FCB7E456" author="Weiss, H. B. &amp; G. M. Ziegler" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" refId="ref11317" refString="Weiss, H. B., and G. M. Ziegler. 1931. Thomas Say, early American naturalist. Charles C. Thomas, Springfield, IL." type="book" year="1931">Weiss and Ziegler 1931</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="6E4D4B784308281CFC87B565FC3DE456" author="Fall, H. C." box="[860,972,858,879]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" pagination="291 - 486" refId="ref11058" refString="Fall, H. C. 1915. A revision of the North American species of Pachybrachys. Transactions of the American Entomological Society 41: 291 - 486." type="journal article" year="1915">Fall (1915)</bibRefCitation>
made no mention of seeing a 
<typeStatus id="D567882B4308281CFCC0B54BFCB5E4B0" box="[795,836,884,905]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">type</typeStatus>
and noted that Bowditch often mistakenly used the name 
<taxonomicName id="CDDC4D0A4308281CFC7BB5B0FBF8E49D" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[928,1033,910,932]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viduatus">
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFC7BB5B0FBF8E49D" box="[928,1033,910,932]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">P. viduatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="CDDC4D0A4308281CFBE8B5B0FB52E49D" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[1075,1187,910,932]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivittatus">
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFBE8B5B0FB52E49D" box="[1075,1187,910,932]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">P. bivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A6336894308281CFD00B596FB70E37A" blockId="7.[707,1194,751,1357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName id="CDDC4D0A4308281CFD00B596FC40E486" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[731,945,937,959]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivittatus">
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFD00B596FC40E486" box="[731,945,937,959]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Pachybrachis bivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the largest, commonest, most widespread, and easily identifiable species in the eastern 
<collectingCountry id="72CB76194308281CFC53B5E0FC48E4CD" box="[904,953,991,1012]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">USA</collectingCountry>
. It is likely found in all 48 contiguous states. 
<bibRefCitation id="6E4D4B784308281CFCB0B5C6FBE4E337" author="Riley, E. G. &amp; S. M. Clark &amp; T. N. Seeno" box="[875,1045,1016,1038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 290" refId="ref11239" refString="Riley, E. G., S. M. Clark, and T. N. Seeno. 2003. Catalog of the leaf beetles of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Megalopodidae, Orsodacnidae and Chrysomelidae, excluding Bruchinae). The Coleopterists Society Special Publication no. 1: 1 - 290." type="journal article" year="2003">
Riley 
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFC78B5C6FC22E337" box="[931,979,1016,1038]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
listed 34 states, five Canadian provinces, and 
<collectingCountry id="72CB76194308281CFC11B22BFBE3E310" box="[970,1042,1044,1065]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. Further research may reveal that multiple species are represented.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A6336894308281CFD00B276FB5BE274" blockId="7.[707,1194,751,1357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">
There are multiple reports of 
<taxonomicName id="CDDC4D0A4308281CFC26B276FB9DE367" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[1021,1132,1096,1118]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivittatus">
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFC26B276FB9DE367" box="[1021,1132,1096,1118]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">P. bivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being found on 
<taxonomicName id="CDDC4D0A4308281CFCC0B25CFC85E341" box="[795,884,1123,1145]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFCC0B25CFCB9E340" box="[795,840,1123,1145]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Salix</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="CDDC4D0A4308281CFCA4B25CFC13E341" box="[895,994,1123,1144]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Salicaceae</taxonomicName>
), which I can confirm from personal experience in 
<collectingRegion id="C818F86B4308281CFC2BB241FBCAE3AA" box="[1008,1083,1150,1171]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C818F86B4308281CFB95B241FB54E3AA" box="[1102,1189,1150,1171]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Colorado</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C818F86B4308281CFD18B2A6FCF6E397" box="[707,775,1177,1198]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Florida</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C818F86B4308281CFCD5B2A6FCA1E397" box="[782,848,1177,1198]" country="United States of America" name="Illinois" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Illinois</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C818F86B4308281CFC8CB2A6FC6CE397" box="[855,925,1177,1198]" country="United States of America" name="Indiana" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Indiana</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C818F86B4308281CFC7EB2A6FC18E397" box="[933,1001,1177,1198]" country="United States of America" name="Kansas" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Kansas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C818F86B4308281CFC2AB2A6FBB8E397" box="[1009,1097,1177,1198]" country="United States of America" name="Nebraska" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Nebraska</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C818F86B4308281CFB8AB2A6FB71E397" box="[1105,1152,1177,1198]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Utah</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="C818F86B4308281CFD18B28CFCD4E3F1" box="[707,805,1203,1224]" country="United States of America" name="Wisconsin" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Wisconsin</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName id="CDDC4D0A4308281CFCF5B28DFBF7E3F1" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[814,1030,1202,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivittatus">
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFCF5B28DFBF7E3F1" box="[814,1030,1202,1224]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Pachybrachis bivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the few species of 
<taxonomicName id="CDDC4D0A4308281CFCEBB2F2FC5CE3DA" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[816,941,1229,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFCEBB2F2FC5CE3DA" box="[816,941,1229,1251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">Pachybrachis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whose biology has been studied in any detail. Egg and larval case formation was reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="6E4D4B784308281CFCBBB33CFC01E221" author="Lawson, F. A." box="[864,1008,1283,1304]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" pagination="942 - 944" refId="ref11112" refString="Lawson, F. A. 1976. Eggs and larval case formation by Pachybrachis bivittatus. Annals of the Entomological Society of America 69 (5): 942 - 944." type="journal article" year="1976">Lawson (1976)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="6E4D4B784308281CFC20B33CFB75E221" author="LeSage, L." box="[1019,1156,1283,1304]" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" pagination="203 - 220" refId="ref11145" refString="LeSage, L. 1985. The eggs and larvae of Pachybrachis peccans and P. bivittatus, with a key to the known immature stages of Nearctic genera of Cryptocephalinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). The Canadian Entomologist 117: 203 - 220." type="journal article" year="1985">LeSage (1985)</bibRefCitation>
described the eggs and larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="CDDC4D0A4308281CFC38B321FBA1E20A" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[995,1104,1309,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivittatus">
<emphasis id="38A8EA9B4308281CFC38B321FBA1E20A" box="[995,1104,1309,1331]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="91">P. bivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and confirmed that larvae feed in the leaf litter of dead willow.
</paragraph>
